{"type":"text","timestamp":1775853619686,"sessionID":"ses_286e10646ffe41oHY4fXJHZaN5","part":{"id":"prt_d791fc6cf001Ec0Ooizr14lpCv","messageID":"msg_d791fa776001GtiKQ3U607DZzP","sessionID":"ses_286e10646ffe41oHY4fXJHZaN5","type":"text","text":"Now I have all the context I need. Let me write the proposal.md for AR-008 following the same format as AR-007.","time":{"start":1775853619684,"end":1775853619684}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775853765069,"sessionID":"ses_286e10646ffe41oHY4fXJHZaN5","part":{"id":"prt_d791fc9e7001vM6RB2co5vpsKp","messageID":"msg_d791fa776001GtiKQ3U607DZzP","sessionID":"ses_286e10646ffe41oHY4fXJHZaN5","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:11","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","content":"# AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement a scheduled garbage collection (GC) mechanism for sandbox resources in `pkg/workloadmanager`. This component periodically scans and cleans up expired, idle, or orphaned sandbox instances to reclaim cluster resources and maintain system health. The GC integrates with the existing Lifecycle Manager (AR-006) and Reconciler Controller (AR-007) to provide configurable retention policies, safe cleanup strategies, and comprehensive observability.\n\nThe garbage collector handles three primary cleanup scenarios:\n1. **TTL Expiration**: Sandboxes that have exceeded their `TTLSecondsAfterFinished` or `MaxLifetimeSeconds`\n2. **Idle Timeout**: Sandboxes that have been inactive longer than `IdleTimeoutSeconds`\n3. **Orphaned Resources**: Sandboxes whose owner references are no longer valid\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Package** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/gc` |\n| **CRDs managed** | `AgentRuntime`, `CodeInterpreter` (runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1) |\n| **Core functionality** | Scheduled GC scans, TTL/idle/orphan detection, safe cleanup with dry-run mode |\n| **Integration with** | client-go listers (cached reads), Lifecycle Manager (AR-006), Reconciler (AR-007) |\n| **Configuration** | Configurable intervals, retention policies, safe-mode dry-run |\n| **Observability** | Prometheus metrics, structured logging, audit events |\n\n### Out of scope\n\n- Sandbox lifecycle management (handled in AR-006)\n- CRD reconciler logic (handled in AR-007)\n- Multi-cluster GC coordination (separate AR)\n- External storage cleanup (e.g., S3 buckets, separate AR)\n- Webhook validation/mutation\n- Helm chart modifications\n\n---\n\n## Design\n\n### File layout\n\n| File | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/gc.go` | **NEW** — GarbageCollector controller, main loop and orchestration |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/scanner.go` | **NEW** — Scan logic for detecting expired/idle/orphaned sandboxes |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/cleaner.go` | **NEW** — Cleanup execution with safety checks and dry-run support |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/config.go` | **NEW** — GC configuration types and validation |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/metrics.go` | **NEW** — Prometheus metrics for GC operations |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/selector.go` | **NEW** — Resource selector utilities for filtering sandboxes |\n\n### Type definitions\n\n**`GarbageCollector`** — Main GC controller:\n\n```go\n// GarbageCollector periodically scans and cleans up sandbox resources.\ntype GarbageCollector struct {\n    // client is the generated typed client for runtime/v1alpha1\n    client runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n    \n    // arLister provides cached read access to AgentRuntimes\n    arLister runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeLister\n    \n    // ciLister provides cached read access to CodeInterpreters\n    ciLister runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterLister\n    \n    // config holds GC configuration\n    config *Config\n    \n    // scanner detects candidates for cleanup\n    scanner *Scanner\n    \n    // cleaner executes cleanup operations\n    cleaner *Cleaner\n    \n    // metrics records GC operations\n    metrics *Metrics\n    \n    // stopCh signals shutdown\n    stopCh chan struct{}\n    \n    // wg waits for goroutines to finish\n    wg sync.WaitGroup\n}\n```\n\n**`Config`** — GC configuration:\n\n```go\n// Config holds garbage collector configuration.\ntype Config struct {\n    // Interval is the GC scan interval (default: 5m)\n    Interval time.Duration\n    \n    // SafeMode enables dry-run mode where no actual deletions occur\n    SafeMode bool\n    \n    // EnableTTLCleanup enables cleanup based on TTL expiration\n    EnableTTLCleanup bool\n    \n    // EnableIdleCleanup enables cleanup based on idle timeout\n    EnableIdleCleanup bool\n    \n    // EnableOrphanCleanup enables cleanup of orphaned resources\n    EnableOrphanCleanup bool\n    \n    // DefaultTTL is the default TTL for sandboxes without explicit TTL\n    DefaultTTL *time.Duration\n    \n    // MaxSandboxAge is the absolute maximum age for any sandbox\n    MaxSandboxAge *time.Duration\n    \n    // BatchSize limits the number of deletions per GC cycle\n    BatchSize int\n    \n    // Parallelism controls concurrent cleanup goroutines\n    Parallelism int\n}\n```\n\n**`Candidate`** — A sandbox candidate for cleanup:\n\n```go\n// Candidate represents a sandbox identified for cleanup.\ntype Candidate struct {\n    // Type is the workload type\n    Type types.WorkloadType\n    \n    // Namespace is the resource namespace\n    Namespace string\n    \n    // Name is the resource name\n    Name string\n    \n    // UID is the resource UID\n    UID string\n    \n    // Reason indicates why this resource is being cleaned up\n    Reason lifecycle.DeletionReason\n    \n    // ExpiredAt is when the resource expired\n    ExpiredAt time.Time\n    \n    // Details contains additional context\n    Details map[string]string\n}\n```\n\n**`ScanResult`** — Result of a GC scan:\n\n```go\n// ScanResult contains the results of a GC scan.\ntype ScanResult struct {\n    // Candidates is the list of sandboxes identified for cleanup\n    Candidates []*Candidate\n    \n    // ScannedTotal is the total number of sandboxes scanned\n    ScannedTotal int\n    \n    // ExpiredCount is the number of expired sandboxes\n    ExpiredCount int\n    \n    // IdleCount is the number of idle sandboxes\n    IdleCount int\n    \n    // OrphanCount is the number of orphaned sandboxes\n    OrphanCount int\n    \n    // ScanDuration is how long the scan took\n    ScanDuration time.Duration\n    \n    // Timestamp is when the scan occurred\n    Timestamp time.Time\n}\n```\n\n### GC Flow\n\n```\nTicker (config.Interval)\n  → Run GC Cycle\n    1. Scan Phase\n       ├── List all AgentRuntimes (cached via lister)\n       ├── List all CodeInterpreters (cached via lister)\n       ├── Check TTL expiration (completionTime + TTLSecondsAfterFinished)\n       ├── Check max lifetime (creationTime + MaxLifetimeSeconds)\n       ├── Check idle timeout (lastActivityTime + IdleTimeoutSeconds)\n       └── Check orphaned (owner references validation)\n    2. Filter Phase\n       ├── Apply retention policies\n       ├── Respect batch size limits\n       └── Sort by expiration time (oldest first)\n    3. Cleanup Phase\n       ├── If SafeMode: log only (dry-run)\n       └── If not SafeMode:\n           ├── Parallel deletion with concurrency limit\n           ├── Update metrics\n           └── Emit audit events\n    4. Report Phase\n       ├── Record scan metrics\n       └── Log summary\n```\n\n### Scanner Implementation\n\n```go\n// Scanner detects sandbox candidates for cleanup.\ntype Scanner struct {\n    arLister runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeLister\n    ciLister runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterLister\n    config   *Config\n}\n\n// Scan performs a full scan and returns candidates for cleanup.\nfunc (s *Scanner) Scan(ctx context.Context) (*ScanResult, error) {\n    start := time.Now()\n    result := &ScanResult{\n        Timestamp: time.Now(),\n        Candidates: make([]*Candidate, 0),\n    }\n    \n    // Scan AgentRuntimes\n    ars, err := s.arLister.List(labels.Everything())\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to list AgentRuntimes: %w\", err)\n    }\n    \n    for _, ar := range ars {\n        result.ScannedTotal++\n        \n        if candidate := s.checkAgentRuntime(ar); candidate != nil {\n            result.Candidates = append(result.Candidates, candidate)\n            \n            switch candidate.Reason {\n            case lifecycle.DeletionReasonTTLExpired:\n                result.ExpiredCount++\n            case lifecycle.DeletionReasonIdleTimeout:\n                result.IdleCount++\n            case lifecycle.DeletionReasonMaxLifetime:\n                result.ExpiredCount++\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    \n    // Scan CodeInterpreters (similar logic)\n    // ...\n    \n    result.ScanDuration = time.Since(start)\n    return result, nil\n}\n\n// checkAgentRuntime evaluates a single AgentRuntime for cleanup.\nfunc (s *Scanner) checkAgentRuntime(ar *v1alpha1.AgentRuntime) *Candidate {\n    now := time.Now()\n    config := lifecycle.ExtractTTLConfigFromAgentRuntime(&ar.Spec)\n    \n    ttlStatus := lifecycle.CalculateTTLStatus(\n        &ar.ObjectMeta.CreationTimestamp,\n        ar.Status.CompletionTime,\n        ar.Status.LastActivityTime,\n        config,\n        now,\n    )\n    \n    if ttlStatus.IsExpired {\n        return &Candidate{\n            Type:      types.WorkloadTypeAgentRuntime,\n            Namespace: ar.Namespace,\n            Name:      ar.Name,\n            UID:       string(ar.UID),\n            Reason:    ttlStatus.ExpirationReason,\n            ExpiredAt: *ttlStatus.ExpirationTime,\n            Details: map[string]string{\n                \"phase\": string(ar.Status.Phase),\n            },\n        }\n    }\n    \n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n### Cleaner Implementation\n\n```go\n// Cleaner executes cleanup operations for GC candidates.\ntype Cleaner struct {\n    client runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n    config *Config\n    metrics *Metrics\n}\n\n// Cleanup performs cleanup for the given candidates.\nfunc (c *Cleaner) Cleanup(ctx context.Context, candidates []*Candidate) (*CleanupResult, error) {\n    result := &CleanupResult{\n        Processed: make([]*Candidate, 0),\n        Failed:    make([]*CandidateError, 0),\n    }\n    \n    // Limit batch size\n    if len(candidates) > c.config.BatchSize {\n        candidates = candidates[:c.config.BatchSize]\n    }\n    \n    // Parallel cleanup with semaphore\n    sem := make(chan struct{}, c.config.Parallelism)\n    var wg sync.WaitGroup\n    \n    for _, candidate := range candidates {\n        wg.Add(1)\n        go func(cand *Candidate) {\n            defer wg.Done()\n            \n            sem <- struct{}{}\n            defer func() { <-sem }()\n            \n            if err := c.deleteCandidate(ctx, cand); err != nil {\n                result.Failed = append(result.Failed, &CandidateError{\n                    Candidate: cand,\n                    Error:     err,\n                })\n                c.metrics.DeletionFailed(string(cand.Type), string(cand.Reason))\n            } else {\n                result.Processed = append(result.Processed, cand)\n                c.metrics.Deleted(string(cand.Type), string(cand.Reason))\n            }\n        }(candidate)\n    }\n    \n    wg.Wait()\n    return result, nil\n}\n\n// deleteCandidate deletes a single candidate.\nfunc (c *Cleaner) deleteCandidate(ctx context.Context, candidate *Candidate) error {\n    // In safe mode, just log and return\n    if c.config.SafeMode {\n        klog.V(2).InfoS(\"GC dry-run: would delete sandbox\",\n            \"type\", candidate.Type,\n            \"namespace\", candidate.Namespace,\n            \"name\", candidate.Name,\n            \"reason\", candidate.Reason,\n        )\n        return nil\n    }\n    \n    // Determine grace period based on reason\n    var gracePeriod *int64\n    if candidate.Reason == lifecycle.DeletionReasonIdleTimeout {\n        // Use shorter grace period for idle sandboxes\n        gp := int64(10)\n        gracePeriod = &gp\n    }\n    \n    // Delete the resource\n    var err error\n    switch candidate.Type {\n    case types.WorkloadTypeAgentRuntime:\n        err = c.client.AgentRuntimes(candidate.Namespace).Delete(ctx, candidate.Name, metav1.DeleteOptions{\n            GracePeriodSeconds: gracePeriod,\n            PropagationPolicy:  ptr.To(metav1.DeletePropagationBackground),\n        })\n    case types.WorkloadTypeCodeInterpreter:\n        err = c.client.CodeInterpreters(candidate.Namespace).Delete(ctx, candidate.Name, metav1.DeleteOptions{\n            GracePeriodSeconds: gracePeriod,\n            PropagationPolicy:  ptr.To(metav1.DeletePropagationBackground),\n        })\n    }\n    \n    if err != nil && !errors.IsNotFound(err) {\n        return err\n    }\n    \n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n### GC Controller Loop\n\n```go\n// Run starts the garbage collector.\nfunc (gc *GarbageCollector) Run(ctx context.Context) error {\n    klog.InfoS(\"Starting garbage collector\", \"interval\", gc.config.Interval)\n    \n    ticker := time.NewTicker(gc.config.Interval)\n    defer ticker.Stop()\n    \n    // Run initial scan immediately\n    gc.runCycle(ctx)\n    \n    for {\n        select {\n        case <-ticker.C:\n            gc.runCycle(ctx)\n        case <-gc.stopCh:\n            klog.Info(\"Stopping garbage collector\")\n            return nil\n        case <-ctx.Done():\n            return ctx.Err()\n        }\n    }\n}\n\n// runCycle executes a single GC cycle.\nfunc (gc *GarbageCollector) runCycle(ctx context.Context) {\n    start := time.Now()\n    klog.V(2).Info(\"Starting GC cycle\")\n    \n    // Scan phase\n    result, err := gc.scanner.Scan(ctx)\n    if err != nil {\n        klog.ErrorS(err, \"GC scan failed\")\n        gc.metrics.ScanFailed()\n        return\n    }\n    \n    gc.metrics.ScanCompleted(result.ScannedTotal, len(result.Candidates), result.ScanDuration)\n    \n    if len(result.Candidates) == 0 {\n        klog.V(2).Info(\"No candidates for cleanup\")\n        return\n    }\n    \n    klog.InfoS(\"GC scan completed\",\n        \"scanned\", result.ScannedTotal,\n        \"candidates\", len(result.Candidates),\n        \"expired\", result.ExpiredCount,\n        \"idle\", result.IdleCount,\n        \"orphan\", result.OrphanCount,\n    )\n    \n    // Cleanup phase\n    cleanupResult, err := gc.cleaner.Cleanup(ctx, result.Candidates)\n    if err != nil {\n        klog.ErrorS(err, \"GC cleanup failed\")\n    }\n    \n    klog.InfoS(\"GC cycle completed\",\n        \"processed\", len(cleanupResult.Processed),\n        \"failed\", len(cleanupResult.Failed),\n        \"duration\", time.Since(start),\n    )\n}\n```\n\n### Metrics\n\n```go\nvar (\n    gcScansTotal = prometheus.NewCounterVec(\n        prometheus.CounterOpts{\n            Name: \"agentcube_gc_scans_total\",\n            Help: \"Total number of GC scan cycles\",\n        },\n        []string{\"result\"},\n    )\n    \n    gcScannedTotal = prometheus.NewCounterVec(\n        prometheus.CounterOpts{\n            Name: \"agentcube_gc_scanned_total\",\n            Help: \"Total number of sandboxes scanned\",\n        },\n        []string{\"workload_type\"},\n    )\n    \n    gcCandidatesTotal = prometheus.NewGaugeVec(\n        prometheus.GaugeOpts{\n            Name: \"agentcube_gc_candidates_total\",\n            Help: \"Number of sandboxes identified for cleanup\",\n        },\n        []string{\"reason\"},\n    )\n    \n    gcDeletedTotal = prometheus.NewCounterVec(\n        prometheus.CounterOpts{\n            Name: \"agentcube_gc_deleted_total\",\n            Help: \"Total number of sandboxes deleted by GC\",\n        },\n        []string{\"workload_type\", \"reason\"},\n    )\n    \n    gcDeletionFailedTotal = prometheus.NewCounterVec(\n        prometheus.CounterOpts{\n            Name: \"agentcube_gc_deletion_failed_total\",\n            Help: \"Total number of failed GC deletions\",\n        },\n        []string{\"workload_type\", \"reason\"},\n    )\n    \n    gcScanDuration = prometheus.NewHistogram(\n        prometheus.HistogramOpts{\n            Name:    \"agentcube_gc_scan_duration_seconds\",\n            Help:    \"GC scan duration in seconds\",\n            Buckets: prometheus.DefBuckets,\n        },\n    )\n    \n    gcCycleDuration = prometheus.NewHistogram(\n        prometheus.HistogramOpts{\n            Name:    \"agentcube_gc_cycle_duration_seconds\",\n            Help:    \"GC cycle duration in seconds\",\n            Buckets: prometheus.DefBuckets,\n        },\n    )\n)\n```\n\n### Default Configuration\n\n| Parameter | Default | Description |\n|-----------|---------|-------------|\n| `Interval` | 5m | GC scan interval |\n| `SafeMode` | false | Dry-run mode (no actual deletions) |\n| `EnableTTLCleanup` | true | Enable TTL-based cleanup |\n| `EnableIdleCleanup` | true | Enable idle timeout cleanup |\n| `EnableOrphanCleanup` | true | Enable orphaned resource cleanup |\n| `BatchSize` | 100 | Max deletions per cycle |\n| `Parallelism` | 10 | Concurrent deletion workers |\n\n### Cleanup Reason Priority\n\nWhen a sandbox matches multiple cleanup conditions, the priority is:\n\n1. **TTL Expired** (highest priority) — `TTLSecondsAfterFinished` exceeded\n2. **Max Lifetime** — `MaxLifetimeSeconds` exceeded\n3. **Idle Timeout** — `IdleTimeoutSeconds` exceeded\n4. **Orphaned** (lowest priority) — owner reference invalid\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Files created/modified\n\n| File | Lines (est.) | Type |\n|------|-------------|------|\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/gc.go` | ~200 | New |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/scanner.go` | ~250 | New |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/cleaner.go` | ~180 | New |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/config.go` | ~100 | New |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/metrics.go` | ~120 | New |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/selector.go` | ~80 | New |\n\n### Downstream consumers\n\n| Consumer | Dependency |\n|----------|-----------|\n| WorkloadManager | GC runs as part of the workload manager |\n| Lifecycle Manager (AR-006) | GC uses lifecycle types for TTL calculation |\n| Reconciler Controller (AR-007) | GC triggers deletions that reconciler handles |\n| Metrics pipeline | Scrapes GC metrics |\n\n### Breaking change risk\n\n- **None for existing APIs**: This is new functionality\n- **SafeMode default**: GC starts in safe mode by default in dev environments\n- **CRD compatibility**: Uses existing TTL/idle fields from CRD specs\n- **Deletion coordination**: GC deletions are handled by existing finalizer logic\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### 1. Use Kubernetes TTL controller instead of custom GC\n\n**Approach**: Rely on the built-in Kubernetes TTL controller for finished resources.\n\n**Rejected because**: The upstream TTL controller only supports Jobs and has limited flexibility. AgentCube needs custom logic for idle detection, orphan cleanup, and per-workload-type retention policies. A custom GC provides better control over the cleanup process and integrates with our metrics/logging infrastructure.\n\n### 2. Event-driven cleanup instead of periodic scanning\n\n**Approach**: Trigger cleanup based on watch events rather than periodic scans.\n\n**Rejected because**: Event-driven cleanup cannot handle \"stuck\" resources or detect idle sandboxes (which require time-based evaluation). Periodic scanning provides a reliable fallback and allows batching deletions for efficiency. A hybrid approach (events + periodic scan) adds complexity without significant benefit.\n\n### 3. Single GC controller for all resource types\n\n**Approach**: Extend the GC to handle Pods, Services, and other related resources directly.\n\n**Rejected because**: This would duplicate the Reconciler's responsibility and create potential conflicts. The GC should only delete CRs (AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter), and let the Reconciler handle cascading cleanup of dependent resources through owner references and finalizers.\n\n### 4. Implement GC as a CronJob instead of in-process\n\n**Approach**: Run GC as a separate Kubernetes CronJob rather than an in-process controller.\n\n**Rejected because**: An in-process controller provides better integration with the WorkloadManager's lifecycle, shared informer caches, and metrics. A CronJob would require separate authentication, lack access to shared caches, and add operational complexity.\n\n### 5. No batch size limit (delete all candidates at once)\n\n**Approach**: Delete all identified candidates in a single cycle without limiting.\n\n**Rejected because**: Large deletion batches can overwhelm the API server and trigger rate limiting. A configurable batch size with parallelism control provides safer, more predictable cleanup behavior.\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Local | Typed client for runtime/v1alpha1 |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | v0.34.1 | Core Kubernetes client |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | v0.34.1 | K8s API machinery (labels, selectors) |\n| `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | v1.x | Metrics collection |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle` | Local | TTL calculation, lifecycle types |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/types` | Local | Workload type definitions |\n\n---\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\n# Unit tests\nmake test PKG=./pkg/workloadmanager/gc/...\n\n# Integration tests\ngo test -v ./pkg/workloadmanager/gc/... -run \"TestGarbageCollector\"\ngo test -v ./pkg/workloadmanager/gc/... -run \"TestScanner\"\ngo test -v ./pkg/workloadmanager/gc/... -run \"TestCleaner\"\n\n# Build verification\ngo build ./pkg/workloadmanager/gc/...\n\n# Verify metrics endpoint\ncurl http://localhost:8080/metrics | grep agentcube_gc\n\n# Verify race conditions\ngo test -race ./pkg/workloadmanager/gc/...\n```\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- [AR-006](#ar-006--sandbox-deletion-and-lifecycle-management) — Sandbox Deletion and Lifecycle Management\n- [AR-007](#ar-007--k8s-reconciler-controller) — K8s Reconciler Controller\n- [client-go library spec](deployment/client-go.md) — Generated client details\n- [Kubernetes Garbage Collection](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/architecture/garbage-collection/) — K8s GC concepts\n- [TTL Controller](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/workloads/controllers/ttlafterfinished/) — K8s TTL controller documentation\n\n---\n\n*AR-008 — Module: pkg/workloadmanager — Language: Go — Size: S*\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-008/spec.yaml":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle/types.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":110,"character":6},"end":{"line":110,"character":17}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"},{"range":{"start":{"line":113,"character":8},"end":{"line":113,"character":19}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"}]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775853764912,"end":1775853765064}}}}
