{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775854027570,"sessionID":"ses_286e10646ffe41oHY4fXJHZaN5","part":{"id":"prt_d7925fe4b001kVpcmU9oklqygH","messageID":"msg_d79220209001Bqe6P7CHJiCFz4","sessionID":"ses_286e10646ffe41oHY4fXJHZaN5","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:12","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","limit":100},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Implement a scheduled garbage collection (GC) mechanism for sandbox resources in `pkg/workloadmanager`. This component periodically scans and cleans up expired, idle, or orphaned sandbox instances to reclaim cluster resources and maintain system health. The GC integrates with the existing Lifecycle Manager (AR-006) and Reconciler Controller (AR-007) to provide configurable retention policies, safe cleanup strategies, and comprehensive observability.\n6: \n7: The garbage collector handles three primary cleanup scenarios:\n8: 1. **TTL Expiration**: Sandboxes that have exceeded their `TTLSecondsAfterFinished` or `MaxLifetimeSeconds`\n9: 2. **Idle Timeout**: Sandboxes that have been inactive longer than `IdleTimeoutSeconds`\n10: 3. **Orphaned Resources**: Sandboxes whose owner references are no longer valid\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Scope\n15: \n16: ### In scope\n17: \n18: | Item | Detail |\n19: |------|--------|\n20: | **Package** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/gc` |\n21: | **CRDs managed** | `AgentRuntime`, `CodeInterpreter` (runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1) |\n22: | **Core functionality** | Scheduled GC scans, TTL/idle/orphan detection, safe cleanup with dry-run mode |\n23: | **Integration with** | client-go listers (cached reads), Lifecycle Manager (AR-006), Reconciler (AR-007) |\n24: | **Configuration** | Configurable intervals, retention policies, safe-mode dry-run |\n25: | **Observability** | Prometheus metrics, structured logging, audit events |\n26: \n27: ### Out of scope\n28: \n29: - Sandbox lifecycle management (handled in AR-006)\n30: - CRD reconciler logic (handled in AR-007)\n31: - Multi-cluster GC coordination (separate AR)\n32: - External storage cleanup (e.g., S3 buckets, separate AR)\n33: - Webhook validation/mutation\n34: - Helm chart modifications\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ## Design\n39: \n40: ### File layout\n41: \n42: | File | Role |\n43: |------|------|\n44: | `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/gc.go` | **NEW** — GarbageCollector controller, main loop and orchestration |\n45: | `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/scanner.go` | **NEW** — Scan logic for detecting expired/idle/orphaned sandboxes |\n46: | `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/cleaner.go` | **NEW** — Cleanup execution with safety checks and dry-run support |\n47: | `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/config.go` | **NEW** — GC configuration types and validation |\n48: | `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/metrics.go` | **NEW** — Prometheus metrics for GC operations |\n49: | `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/selector.go` | **NEW** — Resource selector utilities for filtering sandboxes |\n50: \n51: ### Type definitions\n52: \n53: **`GarbageCollector`** — Main GC controller:\n54: \n55: ```go\n56: // GarbageCollector periodically scans and cleans up sandbox resources.\n57: type GarbageCollector struct {\n58:     // client is the generated typed client for runtime/v1alpha1\n59:     client runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n60:     \n61:     // arLister provides cached read access to AgentRuntimes\n62:     arLister runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeLister\n63:     \n64:     // ciLister provides cached read access to CodeInterpreters\n65:     ciLister runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterLister\n66:     \n67:     // config holds GC configuration\n68:     config *Config\n69:     \n70:     // scanner detects candidates for cleanup\n71:     scanner *Scanner\n72:     \n73:     // cleaner executes cleanup operations\n74:     cleaner *Cleaner\n75:     \n76:     // metrics records GC operations\n77:     metrics *Metrics\n78:     \n79:     // stopCh signals shutdown\n80:     stopCh chan struct{}\n81:     \n82:     // wg waits for goroutines to finish\n83:     wg sync.WaitGroup\n84: }\n85: ```\n86: \n87: **`Config`** — GC configuration:\n88: \n89: ```go\n90: // Config holds garbage collector configuration.\n91: type Config struct {\n92:     // Interval is the GC scan interval (default: 5m)\n93:     Interval time.Duration\n94:     \n95:     // SafeMode enables dry-run mode where no actual deletions occur\n96:     SafeMode bool\n97:     \n98:     // EnableTTLCleanup enables cleanup based on TTL expiration\n99:     EnableTTLCleanup bool\n100:     \n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 642. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement a scheduled garbage collection (GC) mechanism for sandbox resources in `pkg/workloadmanager`. This component periodically scans and cleans up expired, idle, or orphaned sandbox instances to reclaim cluster resources and maintain system health. The GC integrates with the existing Lifecycle Manager (AR-006) and Reconciler Controller (AR-007) to provide configurable retention policies, safe cleanup strategies, and comprehensive observability.\n\nThe garbage collector handles three primary cleanup scenarios:\n1. **TTL Expiration**: Sandboxes that have exceeded their `TTLSecondsAfterFinished` or `MaxLifetimeSeconds`\n2. **Idle Timeout**: Sandboxes that have been inactive longer than `IdleTimeoutSeconds`\n3. **Orphaned Resources**: Sandboxes whose owner references are no longer valid\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Package** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/gc` |","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775854027558,"end":1775854027567}}}}
