{"type":"text","timestamp":1775854079596,"sessionID":"ses_286e10646ffe41oHY4fXJHZaN5","part":{"id":"prt_d7926a96a001BPDkr8tppvfqf1","messageID":"msg_d79260363001CmiOQ2nPa8DOcV","sessionID":"ses_286e10646ffe41oHY4fXJHZaN5","type":"text","text":"I've written the `proposal.md` for AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制. The document includes:\n\n**Key sections:**\n- **Purpose**: Scheduled garbage collection for expired/idle/orphaned sandboxes\n- **Scope**: 6 new files in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/`, integrates with client-go listers\n- **Design**: \n  - `GarbageCollector` controller with ticker-based scan loop\n  - `Scanner` for TTL/idle/orphan detection using existing lifecycle types\n  - `Cleaner` with safe-mode dry-run and parallel deletion\n  - Prometheus metrics for observability\n- **Impact Analysis**: ~930 estimated lines across 6 new files, no breaking changes\n- **Alternatives Considered**: 5 approaches (K8s TTL controller, event-driven, single GC for all types, CronJob, no batch limit) with rejection rationale\n- **Dependencies**: client-go, lifecycle package, types package\n- **Verification**: Unit/integration test commands\n\nThe proposal follows the same format as AR-007 and integrates with the existing `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle` types that already define `TTLConfig`, `DeletionReason`, and `CalculateTTLStatus` functions.","time":{"start":1775854079594,"end":1775854079594}}}
